{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":788,"text":"You may not realize this,"},{"time":2533,"text":"but there are more bacteria in your body\nthan stars in our entire galaxy."},{"time":8040,"text":"This fascinating universe\nof bacteria inside of us"},{"time":11167,"text":"is an integral part of our health,"},{"time":13443,"text":"and our technology is evolving so rapidly"},{"time":15532,"text":"that today we can program these bacteria\nlike we program computers."}]},{"cues":[{"time":21060,"text":"Now, the diagram that you see here,"},{"time":22939,"text":"I know it looks like\nsome kind of sports play,"},{"time":25470,"text":"but it is actually a blueprint of\nthe first bacterial program I developed."},{"time":29626,"text":"And like writing software,\nwe can print and write DNA"},{"time":32947,"text":"into different algorithms\nand programs inside of bacteria."},{"time":36824,"text":"What this program does\nis produces fluorescent proteins"},{"time":39519,"text":"in a rhythmic fashion"},{"time":40957,"text":"and generates a small molecule"},{"time":42559,"text":"that allows bacteria\nto communicate and synchronize,"},{"time":45137,"text":"as you're seeing in this movie."},{"time":47505,"text":"The growing colony of bacteria\nthat you see here"},{"time":49785,"text":"is about the width of a human hair."},{"time":51778,"text":"Now, what you can't see\nis that our genetic program"},{"time":54285,"text":"instructs these bacteria\nto each produce small molecules,"},{"time":57768,"text":"and these molecules travel between\nthe thousands of individual bacteria"},{"time":61181,"text":"telling them when to turn on and off."},{"time":63897,"text":"And the bacteria synchronize\nquite well at this scale,"},{"time":67148,"text":"but because the molecule that synchronizes\nthem together can only travel so fast,"},{"time":71142,"text":"in larger colonies of bacteria,\nthis results in traveling waves"},{"time":74718,"text":"between bacteria that are\nfar away from each other,"},{"time":77620,"text":"and you can see these waves going\nfrom right to left across the screen."}]},{"cues":[{"time":81356,"text":"Now, our genetic program\nrelies on a natural phenomenon"},{"time":84144,"text":"called quorum sensing,"},{"time":85317,"text":"in which bacteria trigger coordinated\nand sometimes virulent behaviors"},{"time":88649,"text":"once they reach a critical density."},{"time":91590,"text":"You can observe quorum sensing\nin action in this movie,"},{"time":94245,"text":"where a growing colony of bacteria\nonly begins to glow"},{"time":97887,"text":"once it reaches a high\nor critical density."},{"time":100258,"text":"Our genetic program"},{"time":102100,"text":"continues producing these\nrhythmic patterns of fluorescent proteins"},{"time":105251,"text":"as the colony grows outwards."},{"time":107619,"text":"This particular movie and experiment\nwe call The Supernova,"},{"time":111310,"text":"because it looks like an exploding star."}]},{"cues":[{"time":114340,"text":"Now, besides programming\nthese beautiful patterns,"},{"time":116730,"text":"I wondered, what else can we get\nthese bacteria to do?"},{"time":119321,"text":"And I decided to explore\nhow we can program bacteria"},{"time":121900,"text":"to detect and treat diseases\nin our bodies like cancer."},{"time":126009,"text":"One of the surprising facts about bacteria"},{"time":128307,"text":"is that they can naturally grow\ninside of tumors."},{"time":131744,"text":"This happens because typically tumors"},{"time":133508,"text":"are areas where the immune system\nhas no access,"},{"time":135923,"text":"and so bacteria find these tumors"},{"time":137920,"text":"and use them as a safe haven\nto grow and thrive."},{"time":141751,"text":"We started using probiotic bacteria"},{"time":143585,"text":"which are safe bacteria\nthat have a health benefit,"},{"time":146209,"text":"and found that\nwhen orally delivered to mice,"},{"time":148670,"text":"these probiotics would selectively\ngrow inside of liver tumors."},{"time":152826,"text":"We realized that the most convenient way"},{"time":154780,"text":"to highlight the presence\nof the probiotics,"},{"time":156861,"text":"and hence, the presence of the tumors,"},{"time":158724,"text":"was to get these bacteria\nto produce a signal"},{"time":160953,"text":"that would be detectable in the urine,"},{"time":163069,"text":"and so we specifically\nprogrammed these probiotics"},{"time":165481,"text":"to make a molecule that would change\nthe color of your urine"},{"time":168360,"text":"to indicate the presence of cancer."},{"time":171170,"text":"We went on to show that this technology"},{"time":173180,"text":"could sensitively and specifically\ndetect liver cancer,"},{"time":176370,"text":"one that is challenging\nto detect otherwise."}]},{"cues":[{"time":179891,"text":"Now, since these bacteria\nspecifically localize to tumors,"},{"time":182890,"text":"we've been programming them\nto not only detect cancer"},{"time":185478,"text":"but also to treat cancer"},{"time":187266,"text":"by producing therapeutic molecules\nfrom within the tumor environment"},{"time":190493,"text":"that shrink the existing tumors,"},{"time":192815,"text":"and we've been doing this\nusing quorum sensing programs"},{"time":195570,"text":"like you saw in the previous movies."}]},{"cues":[{"time":197413,"text":"Altogether, imagine in the future\ntaking a programmed probiotic"},{"time":201110,"text":"that could detect and treat cancer,"},{"time":203589,"text":"or even other diseases."},{"time":206960,"text":"Our ability to program bacteria"},{"time":208604,"text":"and program life"},{"time":210299,"text":"opens up new horizons in cancer research,"},{"time":213248,"text":"and to share this vision,\nI worked with artist Vik Muniz"},{"time":215983,"text":"to create the symbol of the universe,"},{"time":217799,"text":"made entirely out of bacteria\nor cancer cells."},{"time":221443,"text":"Ultimately, my hope is that the beauty\nand purpose of this microscopic universe"},{"time":226645,"text":"can inspire new and creative approaches\nfor the future of cancer research."}]},{"cues":[{"time":231544,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":234168,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}